Dataset: AT&T Face Database (ORL)

Source:
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/kasikrit/att-database-of-faces

Instructions:
1. Download the dataset from Kaggle using the link above.
2. Extract the archive locally.
3. Place the extracted folders into the data directory.
4. Rename the main folder to: train_faces
5. (Optional) Copy one image into a separate test_faces directory for demo usage.

Expected path:
data/train_faces/s1/1.pgm
data/train_faces/s2/1.pgm
...

Optional test image path:
data/test_faces/s1/1.pgm

Notes:
- Images are grayscale (.pgm) with resolution 92x112.
- Face images are NOT included in the repository.
- The dataset is used for classical eigenfaces experiments.

Python Dependencies Required to Run the Project:
- numpy
- matplotlib
- pillow
